Xi Jinping sends congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum - Xinhua News
Xinhua News Beijing December 11th, on December 11th, Chinese president, Xi Jinping, sends congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum.
Xi Jinping pointed out that the world today is undergoing major changes rarely seen in a century; global scientific and technological innovation has entered an intensive and active period; the latest round of scientific and technological revolution and industrial reform have exerted a profound impact on the global economic structure.
The Greater Bay Area of Guangdong, Hong Kong and Macau should center on the strategic positioning of building an international scientific and technological innovation center, strive to build a highland of global scientific and technological innovation, and promote the development of emerging industries.
China is willing to work with scientists, international scientific and technological organizations around the globe to carry out close international scientific and technological exchanges and cooperation, strengthen research on major scientific problems, promote the cracking of common scientific technologies, deepen cooperation on key scientific projects, jointly promote the development of science on a global scale and better benefit mankind.
2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum hosted by Guangdong Province People ’s Government opened that day in Guangzhou, Guangdong with theme “discover the future, share science ” 。
